# ccc-node guard profile — operator-owned. Install explicitly with
# `sudo ./setup.sh --operational-relax` as /etc/ccc-node/guard-profile,
# owned by root:root, mode 0644. Setup remains strict by default, rejects a
# non-root opt-in, and never overwrites an existing operator profile.
#
# The `operational-relax` token below makes ALL operational service/container/
# orchestrator lifecycle (systemctl/service/pm2/docker/podman/kubectl, local or
# toward any peer) and reboot-of-any-host autonomous on this node.
#
# It NEVER relaxes the catastrophic / injection set — catastrophic rm, secret
# exfiltration, protected-branch force-push/history-rewrite, DB destructive/
# migrate/replay, release/publish, repo-visibility, host power-down
# (poweroff/halt), and operator-config writes stay enforced regardless.
#
# Remove this file (or any weaker ownership) to revert the node to strict.
operational-relax
